display.label: SAP S/4HANA Cloud
display.description: SAP S/4HANA is a multi-faceted cloud based ERP solution. Use the S/4HANA component to manage records within the SAP database.

inputs.comments: Follow the next steps to get an API key https://help.sap.com/docs/intelligent-robotic-process-automation/factory-user-guide/add-api-keys-to-environment
inputs.label: SAP API Key

inputs.comments: Provide the Base URL for the organization. Example https://{company-url}.api.sap.com/s4hanacloud
inputs.label: Base URL

documentation.description:
You can create an API key within a single environment and use the API key to execute different public endpoints bound to this specific environment.

While creating an API key, you will be able to see the complete API key and copy/paste into your Prismatic connection. As a best practice, you must store the API key in a safe place so that you can retrieve it in the future. You won’t be able to copy/paste the key once it is added to your environment. Refer to [SAP Help Portal](https://help.sap.com/docs/intelligent-robotic-process-automation/factory-user-guide/add-api-keys-to-environment) for additional Information.

Perform the following steps to create API keys within a single environment.

- Go to the **Environments** tab and click an environment to
open it.
- Go to the **API Keys** section and click Add **API
Key**.
- In the **General** section of **Generate New API Key** window, enter API key name on the Name field and description (optional) on the **Description** field. Click Next.
    
- In the **Scope** section of **Generate New API Key** window, click the toggle button(s) to choose single or multiple scopes of your API key. Click **Next**.
    
- In the **Review** section of **Generate New API Key** window, you can review your API key. Click **Add**. The **Generated Key** dialog box is displayed.
    
- Click **Copy**. The API key will be copied to the clipboard and you can paste it into the Prismatic connection. You can also select the API key manually and copy it.

[Detailed Info Here](https://help.sap.com/docs/intelligent-robotic-process-automation/factory-user-guide/add-api-keys-to-environment)

display.label: Add Attachment
display.description: Uploads an attachment to a business object using the file name, mime type of the attachment, business object type, and business object instance key.

display.label: Get Attachment
display.description: Reads the attachments associated with a document info record.

display.label: Delete Attachment
display.description: Deletes the attachment associated with the business object using the document type, document number, document version, document part, logical document ID, archive document ID, business object type, and business object instance key.

display.label: List Subscriptions
display.description: Reads subscription information for business events.

inputs.comments: Show only the first n items
inputs.label: Top

display.label: Create Subscription
display.description: Creates business event subscriptions.

display.label: Update Subscription
display.description: Updates business events subscription status using the business event subscriber code, SAP object type, SAP object task code, and business event subscription state code.

display.label: List Projects
display.description: Returns details about all customer and internal projects in the system.

display.label: Get Project
display.description: Returns details about a customer or internal project.

display.label: Create Project
display.description: Creates a customer or internal project based on the level of information you provide.

display.label: Update Project
display.description: Updates the basic information for a customer or internal project.

display.label: List Timesheet Entry Collection
display.description: Reads data for all workforce’s timesheet entries. It retrieves information about the time recording made by each workforce’s on a particular task and on a particular day.

inputs.comments: Show only the first n items
inputs.label: Top

display.label: Update Timesheet Entry Collection
display.description: Creates, updates, or deletes workforce timesheet entry based on the data provided in payload.

display.label: List Files
display.description: Retrieves list of prepared files, based on specific filter conditions.

inputs.example: Available values (use one): PackageName, FileName, ObjectName, Scenario, FileSize
inputs.label: Select

display.label: List Change Records
display.description: Retrieves the list of change records in the system.

inputs.comments: Show only the first n items
inputs.label: Top

display.label: Get Change Records
display.description: Reads data of a specific change record based on its universally unique identifier (UUID).

display.label: Create Change Record
display.description: Creates a change record.

display.label: Update Change Record
display.description: Updates header attributes of the change record specified in the request.
